1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:01,810
August 19, 2018

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:04,480
Episode 31

3
00:00:56,950 --> 00:00:59,220
Professor?

4
00:01:03,510 --> 00:01:07,450
Did I wake you up? What to do, I feel so sorry.

5
00:01:07,450 --> 00:01:09,980
Where is your mother?

6
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:13,700
She went out for a while.

7
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,620
Is that so?

8
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:44,490
It's a relief that your condition is better than I thought.

9
00:01:44,490 --> 00:01:50,840
I was in such shock when the accident happened. I really thought you were going to die.

10
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:58,680
But, that day, why did you suddenly run away  as soon as you saw me? Huh?

11
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:05,300
I  just called you because I wanted to talk to you. Was it wrong of me?

12
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:12,800
- No.
- Then why did you do that?

13
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:30,970
Yesterday, you came to my room and took the CD, didn't you?

14
00:02:30,970 --> 00:02:34,670
It was what Yun Yeong Gil left for me.

15
00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:37,740
Is that right?

16
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:41,380
Why did you take that?

17
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:47,680
I was curious. You ran away because you were afraid I would catch you.

18
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:52,530
You know exactly what that's like. Wouldn't someone like you be curious?

19
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:55,490
I asked myself, what is that?

20
00:02:55,490 --> 00:03:01,270
Why, out of all people did the dead man give you that?

21
00:03:01,270 --> 00:03:04,640
What connection do you have with the recent murder case ?

22
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,760
Besides that,

23
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,810
did he give you anything else?

24
00:03:10,810 --> 00:03:15,780
- Why are you curious about that?
- What?

25
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:20,710
- May I ask you something?
- What is it?

26
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:26,110
That day, a year ago,  were you at the scene of the accident where Kim Ian died?

27
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:32,390
What are you talking about now?

28
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:36,260
Because you have a head injury, I see you're really talking nonsense.

29
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:39,960
No.  You were definitely at the scene that day.

30
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:45,820
Although it was raining and dark and I couldn't see that well, I am sure it was you.

31
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:48,570
Hurry and leave.  Hurry up!

32
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,400
Go!

33
00:03:57,290 --> 00:03:59,820
I remember everything.

34
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:06,420
Did you think Yun Yeong Gil hid some evidence in the café?

35
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:09,080
You thought I got it.

36
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:13,560
Didn't you come here to look for it?

37
00:04:14,350 --> 00:04:18,920
Spouting nonsense is evidence? That CD?

38
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:23,130
I'm sorry but there is nothing there.

39
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:27,810
Then why have you come here?

40
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:32,040
You wouldn't ordinarily know or spend time with me.

41
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:37,000
To tell you not to frame a living person with some nonsense that you remember.

42
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,280
Hey!

43
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:53,930
He is a director of our orchestra.

44
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:56,470
Oh, is that so?

45
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:59,840
You've come all the way to the hospital.

46
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:02,370
Would you like something to drink?

47
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:06,410
I'm done.  I have to go now.

48
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:10,050
Take care of yourself.

49
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:58,180
You jerk! What is this? You bastard!

50
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:04,120
Spare me!

51
00:06:10,890 --> 00:06:13,900
What are you doing, Bastard?

52
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:28,250
It was you? What the hell, you bastard?

53
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:32,950
Oh, so noisy. So you got scared, huh?

54
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:35,950
Hey, were you trying to kill me?

55
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:38,930
- This is attempted murder, you bastard.
- So report me.

56
00:06:38,930 --> 00:06:43,950
Do you think that I won't?

57
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:47,740
I found out that you killed my little brother.

58
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,220
You broke up his entire body.

59
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:52,470
I wanted to make you the same as my brother,

60
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:56,630
but I restrained myself.  Do you know why?

61
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:01,320
Because I'm not the same as you.

62
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:06,240
Hey, why are you saying I killed your brother? Who said that?  Nam Ju Won?

63
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,880
Hey, would you believe someone who killed somebody?

64
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:12,780
If you're targeting me as the murderer, show me the evidence!

65
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:14,440
- Evidence?
- Yes

66
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:18,470
Evidence? You think there is no evidence?

67
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:24,370
Here's the evidence.  It's the black box video of you running my brother over with the car.

68
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:27,230
Do you want me to show it to you?

69
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:32,730
Hey. That's funny. What is this bullshit? Nothing remains.

70
00:07:32,730 --> 00:07:38,730
Wrong! Yun Yeong Gil.  It was in Yun Yeong Gil's bag.

71
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:42,600
Do you remember giving him an envelope of money?

72
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:46,450
An envelope full of money with the date of my brother's death written on it..

73
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:50,580
This was in it. You can't believe it?

74
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:55,120
I can't , I can't  believe it.  Why?  Liar.

75
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:58,000
Give it to me. Let me look at it. Asshole.

76
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,830
- Let me have it for a second ...
- You asshole!

77
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,940
My nose.

78
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:10,590
And the ballpoint pen you were searching for. I've looked at everything in it.

79
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:16,270
You stole money from the college? From research funds to fees for cleaning service.

80
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:19,460
Taking and using that money was dirty.

81
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:23,390
So what?

82
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:27,030
I didn't take any of your money.

83
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:33,170
You were afraid you would get caught for embezzlement.

84
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:36,770
Is that why you killed my brother?

85
00:08:36,770 --> 00:08:40,900
I am so sorry for my brother to have died at the hands of someone like you.

86
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:45,710
It's not me.  I said it's not me.

87
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:18,030
Bastard, what the hell are you?

88
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:22,760
Who are you to ask me? Bastard.

89
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:51,820
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

90
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:14,150
Did you see the news?

91
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:16,920
Yes. This evening.

92
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:23,670
The Conductor came by the hospital room. I couldn't meet him, though.

93
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:28,360
I think that may have been right before he was arrested.

94
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:32,540
Before Nam Ju Wan was arrested,

95
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:37,060
he gave me the bag that Yun Yeong Gil was hiding.

96
00:10:37,060 --> 00:10:38,990
A bag?

97
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:43,650
After Yun Yeong Gil died, Nam Ju Wan took the bag he kept in storage.

98
00:10:43,650 --> 00:10:48,610
And I saw it. But in that bag,

99
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:57,780
I found the video which show Ian's last moments while alive.

100
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:02,190
It was inside a money envelope with the date of Ian's death written on it.

101
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:06,550
Money envelope?

102
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:09,560
Goodness...

103
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:14,270
Was Ian's killer's face recorded too?

104
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:19,020
- Yes.
- It's Professor Kang, isn't it?

105
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,790
Yes.

106
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:30,060
Professor Kang came to the hospital.

107
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:32,650
I was sleeping and when I woke up...

108
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:38,430
Professor?

109
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:40,620
Professor Kang was looking down at me.

110
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:42,800
Our eyes met

111
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:49,460
and suddenly, I remembered who was sitting in the back seat of the car Yun Yeong Gil was riding in.

112
00:11:51,230 --> 00:11:53,390
It was Professor Kang.

113
00:11:57,030 --> 00:12:00,870
So you even saw Ian getting killed?

114
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,710
Yes.

115
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,440
Ian saved me that day.

116
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:22,120
He pulled out the knife that had stabbed his stomach, gave it to me, and told me to run away.

117
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,730
To run away and report this.

118
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:25,600
Think straight, Hong Yi Yeong!

119
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:31,100
Listen to me well.

120
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:34,420
And when you see anyone, report this right away.

121
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:36,490
Got it?

122
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,170
And...

123
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:48,530
I don't know how you feel, but I liked you so much.

124
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:52,800
I cannot forgive Professor Kang.

125
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:01,520
I filed a report

126
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:05,380
and gave all the evidence to the police.

127
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,710
Yes.

128
00:13:10,670 --> 00:13:12,700
Will you be alright?

129
00:13:13,950 --> 00:13:15,800
What do you mean?

130
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:23,420
When they begin the investigation again, your stabbing Ian

131
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:27,410
will be revealed, and everyone will know.

132
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:32,310
You may even be investigated as a suspect.

133
00:13:32,310 --> 00:13:34,390
I'm fine.

134
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:38,520
I'm glad I can talk about it, actually.

135
00:13:39,170 --> 00:13:41,880
So don't worry about that.

136
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:52,520
I Wanna Hear Your Song

137
00:14:09,180 --> 00:14:11,700
You are Kang Myeong Seok, aren't you?

138
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:14,100
Looks like you're going to the airport?

139
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,920
Planning to travel abroad, perhaps?

140
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,800
No...

141
00:14:19,890 --> 00:14:22,770
- Get him!
- Kang Myeong Seok !

142
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:25,320
Kang Myeong Seok, stop there!

143
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:33,070
Get him.

144
00:14:34,770 --> 00:14:36,600
Let me go, you bastards.

145
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,360
Do you even know who I am?

146
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:40,670
Notice.

147
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:45,300
Announcement: 20th Anniversary Concert has been temporarily postponed due to internal matters.

148
00:14:48,430 --> 00:14:51,180
This is all quite disturbing.

149
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:56,240
Everyone is preparing to audition for other orchestras.

150
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:59,750
Concertmaster, I bet you have many requests for you to join other orchestras.

151
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:04,190
Even if I leave, I should be the last to go.

152
00:15:04,190 --> 00:15:06,860
Our leader, so loyal.

153
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:08,250
I will be on my way.

154
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:12,540
Has Yi Yeong left the hospital yet? I wasn't able to visit her.

155
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:16,920
She understands the situation, you don't have to worry.

156
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,790
You know some things regarding our investigation of Kang Myeong Seok,

157
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:30,400
-  so we've asked you to come.
- Yes.

158
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:34,910
Last year on August 19, you were at the site of Kim Ian's accident, weren't you?

159
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,460
Yes.

160
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:44,600
Did you stab that person with a knife, by any chance?

161
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:50,060
Yes.

162
00:15:50,060 --> 00:15:52,200
Look at that, I told you!

163
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:56,050
She stabbed Kim Ian.

164
00:15:56,050 --> 00:16:00,140
Please explain the circumstances of your stabbing him.

165
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:06,130
You ran out of the warehouse with him after you were confined there by Yun Yeong Gil?

166
00:16:06,130 --> 00:16:07,830
Yes.

167
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:12,790
We were running away, and when my shoe slipped off,

168
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:18,510
Kim Ian went back to pick it up for me,

169
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:23,230
and at that moment a car rushed towards us.

170
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:29,270
Kim Ian saw that...

171
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:30,940
It's dangerous!

172
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:33,980
... embraced me and we rolled onto the side of the road.

173
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:39,530
And when I came to my senses,

174
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:43,180
the knife that I was holding was stuck in Kim Ian's body.

175
00:16:47,710 --> 00:16:51,410
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry...

176
00:16:53,420 --> 00:16:55,080
These are all lies.

177
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:58,020
You stabbed Kim Ian on purpose, and you are lying about it right now!

178
00:16:58,020 --> 00:17:00,480
Why would I stab him on purpose?

179
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:03,490
if I wanted to kill him, why not stab him in the warehouse?

180
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:09,760
No. With the knife that Conductor gave me, I cut the ropes binding our wrists and we ran away.

181
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:13,860
I saw it clearly.

182
00:17:13,860 --> 00:17:19,050
In the car that rushed towards us, there was this man, sitting in the back seat.

183
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:21,710
I am certain. I am sure.

184
00:17:21,710 --> 00:17:26,110
Hey, Hong Yi Yeong, does that make sense? How could you see my face in the back seat?

185
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:30,780
It was raining so much that night, and there was no light anywhere!

186
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:38,800
You remember quite clearly the weather and the situation from that night.

187
00:17:40,470 --> 00:17:43,360
Send Kang Myeong Seok out for a moment.

188
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:46,090
Hold on, why are you sending me out?

189
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:49,020
If you are going to continue to listen to her lies, why can't I stay?

190
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:51,640
Hey, talk straight.  You stabbed him with a knife!

191
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:55,380
The car just skidded in a puddle of rainwater.

192
00:18:02,330 --> 00:18:04,120
I saw it clearly.

193
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:09,560
In the backseat, it was him sitting there.

194
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:16,860
Nam Ju Wan testified to the same thing. Was that all you saw?

195
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:20,120
Yes.

196
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:27,620
If your testimony is true, what you did is a simple mistake.

197
00:18:27,620 --> 00:18:33,370
And the victim's family did not file any charges against you, so you can go, for now.

198
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:36,630
Yes.

199
00:18:51,190 --> 00:18:54,310
It was difficult to go testify right after work, huh?

200
00:18:54,310 --> 00:18:56,600
No.

201
00:18:56,600 --> 00:19:03,900
Just... I'm a bit sad and it feels empty.

202
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:07,230
What did Kang Myeong Seok say?

203
00:19:07,230 --> 00:19:10,160
He said he didn't kill Ian.

204
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:15,460
That Ian died from me stabbing him.

205
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:19,690
He is capable of saying even worse. Don't concern yourself.

206
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:23,640
Yes.

207
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:28,310
You said you wanted to visit Nam Ju Wan? Let's go, I'll give you a ride.

208
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:31,590
You won't go in with me?

209
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:34,550
I have an engagement, actually.

210
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:41,150
I thought you wouldn't come out to see me.

211
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:46,900
Why wouldn't I? There isn't anything to do in there, anyway. Except to be investigated.

212
00:19:47,610 --> 00:19:52,410
I testified to the events of that day at the police station today.

213
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:57,400
Kang Myeong Seok keeps insisting that it wasn't him.

214
00:19:58,270 --> 00:20:00,890
Yes, he will do that, and more.

215
00:20:01,620 --> 00:20:07,720
Conductor, the reason you hired me as your assistant,

216
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:12,710
it was because you were worried about me, wasn't it?

217
00:20:12,710 --> 00:20:18,720
After thinking about it, I realized that it was very soon after Yun Yeong Gil was released from prison.

218
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:23,870
You were afraid Professor Kang would ask him to do something to me.

219
00:20:23,870 --> 00:20:27,040
You were worried about that, so that was why you hired me, wasn't it?

220
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:34,470
No, I just needed an assistant.

221
00:20:34,470 --> 00:20:40,160
I wanted to monitor you, and I didn't have good intentions.

222
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:42,520
Jang Yun is correct about everything.

223
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:45,840
So you don't have to spin it to make me look good.

224
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:51,730
Because... I am really just a bad guy.

225
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:58,590
I didn't say anything about Ian's death, received money in exchange,

226
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:01,660
and also got a permanent post as conductor.

227
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:06,570
That is me, and that is what I did.

228
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:13,430
But it's not all your fault. Professor Kang caused all this.

229
00:21:13,430 --> 00:21:18,730
Professor Kang and I are the same. We both tried to cover up a wrongdoing.

230
00:21:18,730 --> 00:21:21,270
How am I different?

231
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:23,720
You are different in my eyes.

232
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:29,050
You regret it, don't you?

233
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,840
As you must already know,

234
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:47,410
Sinyeong Group launders money by briefly depositing funds in various Sinyeong Foundation accounts.

235
00:21:47,410 --> 00:21:52,280
Some funds are sent overseas by the foundation and returned to the Group  in the form of foreign investment.

236
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:55,550
Some funds are characterized as Group cultural support donations to the foundation

237
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:59,820
and distributed to a variety of individuals by the foundation.  It's a form of bribery.

238
00:22:00,770 --> 00:22:04,650
And the person deeply involved in all that is Professor Kang.

239
00:22:04,650 --> 00:22:08,040
All those transactions are contained in here.

240
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:12,420
I'm sure someone in Sinyeong Group tried to buy you off,

241
00:22:12,420 --> 00:22:15,080
so why are you bringing this to me?

242
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:18,140
If you served just a few months' prison sentence and kept quiet,

243
00:22:18,140 --> 00:22:20,830
you would have received a large sum in compensation.

244
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:25,800
I thought carefully about all the things that happened here.

245
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:29,580
I just wanted to be involved in music,

246
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:38,430
but the things I pretended not to see caused your son's death.

247
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:42,560
I felt too sorry.

248
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:48,060
It was a short time, but I was grateful. I will take my leave now.

249
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:53,140
Can you please help me?

250
00:22:56,130 --> 00:23:00,990
I want to create a cultural foundation in my deceased son's name.

251
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:06,110
How about paying the price of your crime by working there?

252
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:09,010
I need a new orchestra.

253
00:23:09,010 --> 00:23:12,990
I would be grateful if you helped me.

254
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,470
I'm done with examinations for today.

255
00:23:26,470 --> 00:23:28,950
I know that.

256
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:32,950
I warned you. If you ever appear in front of me again, I will kill you.

257
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:36,970
I am a doctor, I know how to use a blade. Get out of my way.

258
00:23:36,970 --> 00:23:39,180
A blade? How scary.

259
00:23:39,180 --> 00:23:41,880
Also, aren't you a psychiatrist?

260
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,510
Get out of my way right now.

261
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:46,830
Don't be like that, and please forgive me.

262
00:23:46,830 --> 00:23:48,290
I am wrong about everything.

263
00:23:48,290 --> 00:23:51,830
I'm sorry I deceived you when I came to the blind date, and I'm also sorry I for pretending to be a patient.

264
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:55,940
I told you a total of five lies. And I apologize for all of them.

265
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:58,560
You could hit me a hundred times, and I would deserve it.

266
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:02,210
What must I do for you to forgive me?

267
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:08,110
What is your relationship with Jang Yun? Don't try to get away with not answering properly.

268
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,500
A hyung that I know.

269
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,190
Are you two friendly?

270
00:24:13,190 --> 00:24:17,020
Not friends, not brothers, not business partners,

271
00:24:17,020 --> 00:24:19,670
somewhere in the middle of all of those relationships.

272
00:24:19,670 --> 00:24:21,780
What in the world is that?

273
00:24:22,610 --> 00:24:24,790
I don't really know myself.

274
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:29,240
What shall I do? If it will make you feel better, I could do anything.

275
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:31,510
I will do my very best.

276
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:34,400
Then will you sing?

277
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,160
Huh?

278
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:38,090
Stand there and sing a song.

279
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:41,140
Then I will think about whether to stay angry at you or not.

280
00:24:41,140 --> 00:24:42,820
Wh-what song?

281
00:24:42,820 --> 00:24:46,470
Whatever. Stand straight, over there. Hurry.

282
00:24:46,470 --> 00:24:48,470
Over there?

283
00:24:48,470 --> 00:24:51,350
- Right here?
- You have to sing the song from the beginning to the end.

284
00:24:51,350 --> 00:24:54,210
Now, start.

285
00:24:55,390 --> 00:24:58,220
Say... say, say, say...

286
00:24:58,220 --> 00:25:00,000
say, say, say, say!

287
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,140
I will begin.

288
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:08,780
One, two, one two, three, four.

289
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:13,020
♪ The moment I first saw you
("Honey" by Park Jin Yeong)

290
00:25:13,020 --> 00:25:17,140
What the? He's really singing it?
♪ I couldn't move

291
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:18,180
Oh, I'm so embarrassed.

292
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:20,820
♪ Your beauty

293
00:25:20,820 --> 00:25:25,660
♪ Made me lose my senses

294
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:28,150
♪ Your beautiful

295
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:33,150
♪ smile at that time, captured me

296
00:25:34,460 --> 00:25:36,950
♪ Now everybody party

297
00:25:36,950 --> 00:25:40,500
You must have been surprised that I suddenly called.

298
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:42,060
No, it's fine.

299
00:25:42,060 --> 00:25:48,320
I behaved badly to you, didn't I, Jang Yun?

300
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:53,200
I spoke harshly to you because you were a murder suspect, and I hit you and told you not to come to the hospital.

301
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,170
I'm very sorry about that.

302
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:58,660
No, it's fine. I understand.

303
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:03,070
I've watched the news and read news articles

304
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:09,310
and even asked my daughter, so I learned the whole story.

305
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:15,450
In any case, I'm glad everything worked out.

306
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:20,020
I'm also grateful that you didn't file charges against our niece.

307
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:26,500
And please let your parents know

308
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:34,630
that we are so sorry that our niece wounded their dead child's body,

309
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:36,940
and we are also so grateful.

310
00:26:36,940 --> 00:26:41,500
I will make sure to visit your brother's final resting place.

311
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:45,290
With Yi Yeong, to request his forgiveness.

312
00:26:45,290 --> 00:26:50,880
You don't have to be so concerned. I received so much help from Yi Yeong all this time.

313
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:56,430
But still, parents don't feel that way.

314
00:26:56,430 --> 00:27:00,830
I'm sure they are deeply aggrieved.

315
00:27:01,530 --> 00:27:07,050
But since all the bad things have passed, I hope only good things will happen to all of us.

316
00:27:07,050 --> 00:27:11,070
That your work will go well, that you will meet someone good,

317
00:27:11,070 --> 00:27:14,180
and enjoy a lovely relationship.

318
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:18,180
Then, please go safely.

319
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:39,380
I hope that our Yi Yeong will meet someone ordinary,

320
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:48,350
someone without baggage... just someone who cherishes her.

321
00:27:49,140 --> 00:27:52,990
Since she met you, Jang Yun, I don't recall ever seeing Yi Yeong smile happily.

322
00:27:52,990 --> 00:27:56,880
She always looked pained.

323
00:28:09,570 --> 00:28:11,990
I plan on moving back to my old place soon.

324
00:28:11,990 --> 00:28:14,190
I don't think anything will happen, anymore,

325
00:28:14,190 --> 00:28:17,410
and I should begin to prepare for my audition in the fall, too.

326
00:28:17,410 --> 00:28:20,800
What? Are you playing timpani or whatever, again?

327
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,350
Oh, give up on that.

328
00:28:24,530 --> 00:28:28,290
Even hearing the "O" of "orchestra" makes my heart tremble with fear.

329
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:31,170
Goodness, leave her be.

330
00:28:31,170 --> 00:28:35,060
She's done this all her life. If she quits, what else will she do?

331
00:28:36,490 --> 00:28:38,630
She can work in our flower shop.

332
00:28:38,630 --> 00:28:41,280
Stay by my side, then get married.

333
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:45,820
Honey, you're a 21st century person, speaking like a 19th century person.

334
00:28:45,820 --> 00:28:49,760
In any case, it's her life. Let her do what she wants.

335
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:01,340
Tone Deaf Man: Let's hang out together and have fun, it's been so long. Come out.

336
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:07,640
This is all because of you. I always thought it was weird that she was pounding on those drums.

337
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:10,560
Why would a young girl bang on a drum?

338
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:13,560
It's not a drum, it's timpani. How ignorant.

339
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,320
Oh, goodness.

340
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:18,230
Oh, I'm so full. I enjoyed the meal.

341
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:24,330
What is this?

342
00:29:25,540 --> 00:29:27,690
Are we going somewhere?

343
00:29:27,690 --> 00:29:31,960
I plan on feeding you plenty of meat today.

344
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,540
What in the world?

345
00:29:33,540 --> 00:29:38,010
If you behave unusually, they say you are sick. Are you okay?

346
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:40,040
Get in.

347
00:29:40,770 --> 00:29:42,780
I love it.

348
00:29:58,420 --> 00:30:02,300
How is your health? Are you eating well?

349
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,520
Of course.

350
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:07,960
I eat well here,  you don't have to worry.

351
00:30:10,550 --> 00:30:16,860
As we live our lives, it's possible to fall into a ditch.

352
00:30:16,860 --> 00:30:20,480
It doesn't mean your life is over, though.

353
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:25,590
And you've still got me by your side.

354
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:31,580
So while you're in here, do your best.

355
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,470
Yes.

356
00:30:37,710 --> 00:30:40,160
Now you two talk amongst yourselves.

357
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:43,690
I will be outside.

358
00:30:49,780 --> 00:30:52,160
What a sight.

359
00:30:53,750 --> 00:30:55,780
Those clothes suit you.

360
00:30:55,780 --> 00:31:00,350
You must not have wanted to see me, but thanks for coming, and bringing Grandma, too.

361
00:31:00,350 --> 00:31:03,010
No need for such politeness.

362
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:07,370
I said some harsh things to you.

363
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:10,820
I suspected you of killing Kim Ian,

364
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:14,340
and even asked that you be fired from Sinyeong Philharmonic.

365
00:31:16,970 --> 00:31:21,260
Yes, you hated me.

366
00:31:21,260 --> 00:31:25,670
Look, you don't know anything.

367
00:31:25,670 --> 00:31:31,160
I didn't hate you, it was because I liked you.

368
00:31:34,450 --> 00:31:38,100
So keep your promise to me.

369
00:31:38,100 --> 00:31:39,800
What promise?

370
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:44,230
Next time we see each other, you said we should be smiling.

371
00:31:46,850 --> 00:31:48,590
Mmm.

372
00:31:53,820 --> 00:31:56,350
This place is so pretty.

373
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:06,550
Have you been camping before?

374
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:10,910
During school, a few times. What about you?

375
00:32:10,910 --> 00:32:15,970
Today is my first time. I'm trembling with excitement.

376
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:20,510
- It smells good.
- These are all cooked. Eat some.

377
00:32:23,170 --> 00:32:25,730
I should feed them to you.

378
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:38,890
It's hot, hot...

379
00:32:41,070 --> 00:32:44,960
Is it good?

380
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,870
Your turn, say ah.

381
00:32:46,870 --> 00:32:49,990
♫ Because your calm eyes are deeper than a lake ♫

382
00:32:49,990 --> 00:32:51,210
Oh, come on.

383
00:32:51,210 --> 00:32:54,940
♫ If you say something sad ♫

384
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:56,830
♫ you are swayed like a wave ♫

385
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,760
This is very tasty.

386
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:02,760
Let's eat all this, and I'll cook the next batch.

387
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:03,990
No, I'll do it.

388
00:33:03,990 --> 00:33:07,080
- No, I'll do it.
- I'll do it.

389
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:09,560
You just had a serious look.

390
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,760
No. I'll do it, Ma'am.

391
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:14,830
You're speaking formally to me, now?

392
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:16,530
I'll do it, you just eat.

393
00:33:16,530 --> 00:33:18,960
♫ l'll live looking forward to eternity ♫

394
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:24,550
♫ I wonder if someday you will look back at me. ♫

395
00:33:25,930 --> 00:33:32,350
♫ It's okay even once in a while if your voice is soft ♫

396
00:33:33,490 --> 00:33:34,840
♫ Please let me hear your song ♫

397
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:37,450
We should draw pictures now.

398
00:33:37,450 --> 00:33:40,500
I will draw a picture for you. Watch.
♫ So that I can love you more ♫

399
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:45,730
Star.
♫ I will treasure it alone for a long time ♫

400
00:33:45,730 --> 00:33:48,790
Next, a heart.
♫ Before thie feeling wanes ♫

401
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:54,420
Or, "Yun is an idiot."
♫ Please take my hand so that I won't get weary ♫

402
00:33:54,420 --> 00:33:57,390
Idiot.
♫ You take me all ♫

403
00:33:57,390 --> 00:34:00,260
This is nice, this is fun.

404
00:34:00,260 --> 00:34:03,320
I'm so excited. Look at me. Wow.

405
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:06,700
It's so pretty.

406
00:34:06,750 --> 00:34:09,540
♫ You take me all ♫
